{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9f82b041-9ebc-4434-89ef-bfe3889baa08","content":"The template is **structurally valid** but has a few gaps before it's NuGet-ready:\n\n**Missing recommended fields:**\n\n| Field | Why it matters |\n|---|---|\n| `$schema` | Enables editor validation (`https://json.schemastore.org/template`) |\n| `groupIdentity` | Required for clean install/update/uninstall of template packs |\n| `description` | Critical for discoverability on NuGet — users see this in `dotnet new search` |\n| `preferNameDirectory` | Controls whether `dotnet new` creates a subdirectory (typically `true` for project templates) |\n\n**Other notes:**\n- `identity`, `shortName`, `sourceName`, `author`, `tags` — all look good.\n- The `Framework` symbol with `net8.0`/`net9.0` choices is fine.\n- You'll also need a `.csproj` or `.nuspec` to actually produce the NuGet package (the template content alone isn't packable).\n\n**Suggested additions:**\n```json\n\"$schema\": \"https://json.schemastore.org/template\",\n\"groupIdentity\": \"MyCompany.WebApi.CSharp\",\n\"description\": \"A template for creating a Web API project.\",\n\"preferNameDirectory\": true\n```\n\nWould you like me to apply these changes?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"24e03d5d-cc8e-4c59-b4b4-6a3bc68a308f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Let me review the template.json for NuGet publishing readiness. I'll check for required and recommended fields according to the .NET template engine spec.\n\nIssues I can see:\n\n1. **Missing `$schema`** – Not strictly required, but recommended for validation and editor support.\n2. **Missing `groupIdentity`** – Recommended for NuGet template packs so templates can be updated/uninstalled properly.\n3. **Missing `precedence`** – Useful when multiple versions of a template exist.\n4. **Missing `preferNameDirectory`** – Common recommendation.\n5. **`defaultValue` references `net9.0`** – This is fine if .NET 9 is the intended default (it was released Nov 2024, so by May 2026 it's current).\n\n\n6. **No `description`** – This is important for discoverability on NuGet.\n7. **No `postActions`** – Not required, but worth noting if restore is needed.\n\nThe critical gaps for NuGet publishing are the missing `$schema`, `groupIdentity`, and `description` fields. The user specifically asked about template.json, so I won't dig into .nuspec or .csproj files unless needed.\n\nThe template is structurally sound but lacks several recommended metadata fields like `preferNameDirectory` that would improve template pack management and NuGet discoverability.","outputTokens":734,"requestId":"7823:339FE5:BAED4C:D892B0:69F3FBA7"},"id":"ca8c11c5-e3c8-421b-ac51-5b50cf74b0aa","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:02:48.721Z","parentId":"5483e7e4-ff96-4a04-8385-dc38e60d35c5"}
